import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by=['date'])
    data = data.groupby(['date'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['rate'], color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('What is the overall trend of unemployment rates across all industries from 2000 to 2010?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y')
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'series'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    data = data.pivot(index='year', columns='series', values='rate')
    data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True)
    plt.title('Which industry had the highest unemployment rate in a given year?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Industry', bbox_to_anchor=(1.05, 1), loc='upper left')
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['rate'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['rate'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['rate'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rates across all industries?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['month_year'] = data['date'].dt.strftime('%Y-%m')
    year = 2000
    for i in range(11):
        year_data = data[data['year'] == year]
        plt.plot(year_data['month_year'], year_data['rate'], label=year)
        year += 1
    plt.xlabel('Month-Year')
    plt.ylabel('Unemployment Rate')
    plt.title('How does the unemployment rate vary across different months of a given year?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'series'])['count'].sum().reset_index()
    max_count = data['count'].max()
    max_count_series = data.loc[data['count'] == max_count, 'series'].values[0]
    max_count_year = data.loc[data['count'] == max_count, 'year'].values[0]
    data = data.pivot(index='series', columns='year', values='count')
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(12, 6), rot=0)
    ax.set_xlabel('Industry')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of unemployed people')
    ax.set_title('Which industry had the highest number of unemployed people in a given year?')
    ax.axhline(y=max_count, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Max count: {max_count:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
